SILENCER DETAILS:
The Ti-RANT .45 is the world’s first silencer for .45 ACP pistols that is truly stealthy when fired dry. The average dry sound signature of the Ti-RANT .45 is 133 dB when fired on a Heckler and Koch USP Tactical .45 with Remington 230 grain ammunition. This puts the dry performance of the Ti-RANT .45 squarely in the ballpark of most competitor's 9mm pistol silencers. With a wet charge of 5cc’s of water, the sound signature drops to 125 dB. To put it another way, our .45 silencer is quieter than some company’s .22 silencers. The Ti-RANT .45 does not stand out among a sea of posers just because of its jaw-dropping performance. Intelligent material selection gives the Ti-RANT .45 unequalled durability in a deceptively light-weight package. 

The Ti-RANT .45 incorporates AAC’s new A.S.A.P.™ CLUTCH. This highly evolved Nielsen device enables flawless semi-automatic operation on all relevant host pistols, and can be fully disassembled for cleaning or piston replacement with no tools in seconds. The Ti-RANT .45 can be outfitted with pistons threaded M16 x 1 Right Hand, M16 x 1 Left Hand, and two pistons threaded .578-28; one extended for the Sig P-220 and 1911’s with a full length guide rod, and a flush mount for 1911’s with a standard G.I. guide rod. For multi-caliber use, pistons are available in the most common 9mm and .40 thread patterns to allow use of the Ti-RANT 45 on hosts in those calibers.

PISTON(S) DETAILS:

There is a "SHORT" model piston, designed only for use on 1911 pistols WITHOUT a full-length guide rod and on the FN FNP Tactical 45.

postcontent:
The Witness P-S may be one of the best kept shooting secrets these days.

It’s not the Pavona or the Compact.

It’s full size, but it has a thin grip.  Even people that don’t have huge hand can comfortably grip and shoot this gun.  Even with the smallish grip, it still holds 16 + 1.

The P is for polymer and the S is for either great ergonomic small frame or standard frame, which is smaller than the huge grips that many folks have a hard time shooting.

The slide riding inside the frame, like a CZ 75, cuts down on recoil and makes it easier to shoot and control.

Black slide, but the frame is pretty neat dark blue color.  The Blue is very difficult to find.

24 oz with no magazine and 32 oz with a fully loaded magazine and one in the pipe

title: For Sale:  Witness P-S 9mm
location: NW San Antonio, San Antonio, Texas
postcontent:
The Witness P-S may be one of the best kept shooting secrets these days.

It’s not the Pavona or the Compact.

It’s full size, but it has a thin grip.  Even people that don’t have huge hand can comfortably grip and shoot this gun.  Even with the smallish grip, it still holds 16 + 1.

The P is for polymer and the S is for either great ergonomic small frame or standard frame, which is smaller than the huge grips that many folks have a hard time shooting.

The slide riding inside the frame, like a CZ 75, cuts down on recoil and makes it easier to shoot and control.

Black slide, but the frame is pretty neat dark blue color.  The Blue is very difficult to find.

24 oz with no magazine and 32 oz with a fully loaded magazine and one in the pipe

Tanfoglio makes it in Italy, but EAA imports it.

Can be converted to a .22lr or 40 cal.

EAA Witness PS Full-size Model Semi-Auto Pistol • 9mm • 4.5" Barrel • Blue Finish • Lightweight Black Polymer Frame • 3-Dot Fixed Sights • Ergonomic Grip • Cock and Lock Design • Extended Safety & Mag Release • Competition Hammer & Trigger • Built-In Tactical Accessory Rail • 1-16rd Hi-Capacity Magazine

title: For Sale:  Public Service Announcement!
postcontent:
Hello. I am like some of you on here who buys, sells and trades guns on Armslist. I have had an account since 2012. I have bought, sold and traded over 100 firearms in that time span until now. 
When I first started, I would price my guns $40-$50 lower than the average national on every other similar Armslist listing. And people who saw what I had for sell back then knew that I was giving a deal. They would call, buy it for what I asked and on their merry way. 

Well, here in the last 6 months, we have had an influx of cheap stupidity coming mostly from under 25 year olds, but I also have seen it from the older crowd. Recently made a deal on a S&W .38 revolver I had for sell. I had it for $300. They go for $365. Guy in his 50's in a blue Subaru said he had $280. I met up with him and he pulled out $265. This is after he threw the gun in his passenger seat from his driver's door. It's just been slipping on here as far as good, decent people.

 It is really despicable(I just spit when I said that like Sylvester the Cat) to have a great price up there and some BillyBob from Brent tell you "he'll go" X amount of dollars--- that is like $150 cheaper than your price. And then want you to drive halfway to meet them. Hahaha. Nope. Sorry you disrespectful degenerate. You're not going to insult anyone else with your Craigslist, flea market mentality. 

This is a reputable firearms site. It is not Craigslist. Because Craigslist restricts the selling or trading of firearms, I guess those creeps come here. If you see a good deal that you know is a good deal, don't be "that guy" who tries to see just how free you can get something. You are not Monty Hall. This is not Neverland. 

*If you email me and your name pops up, I Google that name before I meet you to sell a gun. If your Facebook page shows you standing in Walmart with gold teeth throwing gang signs with your pants sagging, then I just put you in the "you're an idiot I will not meet" category.

*If you tell me that you can buy a brand new one for that price, THEN GO BUY IT! I don't care what the Taurus rebate is or if your uncle knows a guy at Colt. I really don't care. If you can go do that, then why are you telling me about it? I only care if you are giving me the money I want. That's the only time I care. 

*Oh, and stop telling me, " I'll give you $---- CASH!" Do you think I'm taking a personal check? Or swiping your card when we meet up? Of course it's cash. That's the only option available here you dummy. Stop thinking that is an advantage or incentive to take your low ball offer. Duhhhhhhhhhhhhh!!!!!!!

OK, this concludes this PSA. Have a nice day and please stop being cheap. There's haggling and then there is just being a jerk. It is a thin line. It is disrespectful and insulting when crossed.

The G2 is a great platform to make the ultimate "go bag." It is relatively compact, yet capable of internally storing a sniper rifle or an M-16/M-4/AR type weapon, water, ammo, and survival gear. Once in the field, the pack has good capacity, but has the added benefit of being really easy to lash additional gear to, simply by cranking on an external load with its built-in compression straps. The top pocket assembly features a handy internal organizer, with several small pockets, pen holders, and a padded pocket which serves equally well for AR mags or for a PDA."On Amazon, the Coyote Brown version is going for $330. This bag is very lightly used, shows no wear, and is in like new condition. Included for free is the Eberlestock Saddle Bag, which is $28 on Amazon.
